## What is Sentiment Analysis?

Sentiment analysis — also called opinion mining — is the process of using computer algorithms to automatically determine the emotional tone behind a piece of text. It is one of the most widely used applications of Natural Language Processing in the real world.

Every day, millions of customers leave product reviews on platforms like Amazon, Daraz, and eBay. Reading all of them manually is impossible. Sentiment analysis solves this by letting a machine read thousands of reviews in seconds and instantly tell a business how their customers feel. Companies use this technology to track product quality, identify problems early, compare competitor feedback, and make data-driven decisions.

In this project, we build a sentiment classifier that takes any product review as input and outputs one of three labels: Positive, Negative, or Neutral.

